  "name": "Morrison COU2 — Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending MRL-5 fully-assessed credibility package",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct at Model Risk Level 5. This package constitutes COU2 in the Morrison archetype series: the validated FEA ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes solvers) is applied to predict construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are assessed at the highest rigor level required by MRL 5. Full uncertainty quantification (Monte Carlo propagation, sensitivity analysis via Sobol indices) is documented and linked. Validation is grounded in N=11 experimental constructs across two independent laboratories. Decision outcome is Accepted based on all factors meeting or exceeding required levels and E/uval < 1.96 across all quantities of interest.",
